From bb9cfb6d2f3afa6edf30d38932d3b4dd2a3cc05e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yuvasree Sivasankaran <ysivasan@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Sep 2025 10:14:47 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:DP:wifi:ath12k: Fix tx_enqueue counter in device dp
 stats

A new api is added to handle fast tx packets and new counter is
accounted for the same. But the new counter is not accounted in
debugfs tx_enqueue counter to hold all tx related counters.

Add fast tx counter to debugfs tx_enqueue counter.

Patch Dependency:
0378-QSDK-DP-wifi-ath12k-Tx-Enqueue-Optimization.patch

Fixes: Ie43df641fba (QSDK: DP: wifi: ath12k: Tx KPI Optimizations)

Signed-off-by: Yuvasree Sivasankaran <ysivasan@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/debugfs.c | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/debugfs.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/debugfs.c
index 44cfa61..235c30c 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/debugfs.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/debugfs.c
@@ -884,7 +884,9 @@ static ssize_t ath12k_debugfs_dump_device_dp_stats(struct file *file,
 
 	for (i = 0; i < DP_TCL_NUM_RING_MAX; i++)
 	       tx_enqueued[i] = device_stats->tx_mcast[i] + device_stats->tx_unicast[i] +
-		                 device_stats->tx_eapol[i] + device_stats->tx_null_frame[i];
+				device_stats->tx_eapol[i] +
+				device_stats->tx_null_frame[i] +
+				device_stats->tx_fast_unicast[i];
 
 	for (i = 0; i < DP_REO_DST_RING_MAX; i++) {
 		for (j = 0; j < ATH12K_MAX_SOCS; j++)
-- 
2.34.1

